snippet: The Smithsonian National Zoo discloses the results of a final necropsy.
abstract: The Smithsonian National Zoo discloses the results of a final necropsy.
lead_paragraph: The Smithsonian National Zoo has concluded after a final necropsy that lung and liver damage caused the death of a six-day-old panda cub at the zoo last month. “Her lungs were poorly developed and likely caused her to have insufficient oxygen,” which would be consistent with the hardness they had noted in some places in the cub’s liver, it said. The zoo added that the cub’s mother, Mei Xiang, is in good health and eating normally.

headline.main: Panda Cub Died of Lung and Liver Damage
